Pyongyangites swear revenge 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 6 (KCNA) -- Workers of the Pyongyang Vinyl Chloride Shoes Factory, Pyongyang Changgwang Garments Factory and Pyongyang Silk Mill held rallies and bitterly condemned murderers of the U.S. army and South Korean authorities, shouting "Let us make the enemy pay for the blood of the murdered South Korean women a thousand times "   on January 27, a non-commissioned officer of the Naval Intelligence Service of the U.S. 8th army brutally killed a woman and her 4-year-old girl in Seoul, and on the 30th, soldiers of the U.S. aggression forces raped a woman Sin Cha Gum in Tongduchon, Kyonggi Province, and strangled her to death.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the rallies, speakers said that they could not pardon the U.S. imperialist aggressors for enjoying  pleasures after turning South Korea into a center of prostitution and slaughter.
   They stressed that all the employees of the factories would certainly square accounts with the U.S. 
   They said that the South Korean authorities, who are prolonging their remaining days by serving the U.S. imperialist cannibals as if they were their real grandfathers, are a group of traitors devoid of any national spirit and blood. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The outrageous acts of the U.S. against the South Korean people are being encouraged by the present South Korean authorities who curry favour with them, they said, adding:   All the Korean women will certainly bring the murderers of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces to the justice of history and make them pay thousand-fold prices for their crimes.
